      "content": "exactly. it feels intentional. like, if they found something massive—like an actual structure or proof of something ancient—the public wouldn't be able to handle the paradigm shift. how would an agency even start to scrub that much data? what kind of specific patterns or 'sanitized' files should i be looking for to prove this isn't just a coincidence?",
